4. Brick Sort :
Brick Sort ek comparison-based sorting algorithm hai jo array ko pair-wise compare karke sort karta hai similar to bubble sort but in this we compare indexes—
pehle odd index pairs compare karta hai, fir even index pairs, aur ye process tab tak chalta rehta hai jab tak array sorted nahi ho jata.
Isse Odd-Even Sort bhi kehte hain ya fir parity sort.
                       ⚙️ Steps to Implement Brick Sort :
                                              1️⃣ Repeat until no swap happens →
                                                           Hum overall loop tab tak chalate hain jab tak poora array sorted nahi ho jata.
                                                           Ek boolean flag use karte hain: isSorted = false; then while(!isSorted) { isSorted= true) both loop inside it}.
                                              2️⃣ Odd Phase → Compare odd-index pairs
                                                            Odd phase me hum (index 1,2), (3,4), (5,6) ko compare karte hain:
                                                             for (int i = 1; i <= n-2; i += 2)
                                                                      if(arr[i] > arr[i+1])
                                                                          swap(arr[i], arr[i+1])
                                                                          isSorted=false;
                                              3️⃣ Even Phase → Compare even-index pairs
                                                             Even phase me hum (index 0,1), (2,3), (4,5) ko compare karte hain:
                                                                for (int i = 0; i <= n-2; i += 2)
                                                                     if(arr[i] > arr[i+1])
                                                                        swap(arr[i], arr[i+1])
                                                                          isSorted=false;
                                              4️⃣ If no swaps in both phases → sorted
                                                              Agar odd + even phases me ek bhi swap nahi hua → array sorted.
                                              5️⃣ Continue until sorted
                                                              Odd → Even → Odd → Even repeatedly Jab tak array sorted nahi ho jaye.
                                              6️⃣ Final Result →
                                                             Example: 4,3,2,1
                                                             After many odd/even rounds → 1,2,3,4
✅ Time Complexity = O(n2)
